        "title": "Introduction to ADB (Android Debug Bridge)",
        "excerpt":"üéØ Learning Objectives   Understand what ADB is and why it is useful.  Install and configure ADB on macOS.  Connect an Android phone using ADB.  Perform basic ADB operations such as listing files, transferring files, and accessing device shell.1. üîç What is ADB? ADB (Android Debug Bridge) is a command-line tool that allows communication between your computer and an Android device. It is used by developers and advanced users to:   Debug apps  Transfer files  Access internal system logs  Run shell commands on the Android device2. ‚öôÔ∏è Installation on macOS Step 1: Install Homebrew (if not already installed) /bin/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)\"Step 2: Install ADB using Homebrew brew install android-platform-tools3. üì≤ Enable USB Debugging on Android On Your Phone (e.g., Oppo F7):   Go to Settings &gt; About Phone  Tap Build Number 7 times to enable Developer Options  Go to Settings &gt; Additional Settings &gt; Developer Options  Enable USB Debugging4. üîå Connect Phone to Mac   Use a USB data cable  Set USB mode to File Transfer (MTP)  Accept ‚ÄúAllow USB debugging‚Äù prompt on your phone5. üíª Verify ADB Connection Command: adb devicesExpected output: List of devices attachedABC1234567\tdeviceIf it says unauthorized, check your phone for the prompt and tap Allow. 6. üß™ Common ADB Commands üìÇ List files on phone storage: adb shell ls /sdcard/üñ•Ô∏è Start a shell session inside the phone: adb shellüì§ Copy file from phone to Mac: adb pull /sdcard/DCIM/Camera/IMG_20230605_103214.jpg ~/Pictures/üì• Copy file from Mac to phone: adb push myfile.pdf /sdcard/Download/üßπ Delete a file from phone: adb shell rm /sdcard/Download/myfile.pdf7. üì∏ Access Camera Folder View contents: adb shell ls /sdcard/DCIM/CameraCopy all camera images: adb pull /sdcard/DCIM/Camera ~/Pictures/OppoCamera8. üß∞ Optional: Automate with a Script You can create a simple sync script to pull new photos from your phone automatically. Ask the instructor for details. üìù Summary             Task      Command                  Install ADB      brew install android-platform-tools              Connect device      adb devices              Enter phone shell      adb shell              List phone files      adb shell ls /sdcard/              Pull file from phone      adb pull &lt;source&gt; &lt;destination&gt;              Push file to phone      adb push &lt;source&gt; &lt;destination&gt;              Delete file      adb shell rm &lt;path&gt;      üìö References   Official Android ADB Docs  man adb (if installed via Homebrew)","categories": ["Android Development","Terminal Tools"],
