        "title": "Mermaid demo",
        "excerpt":"Want to add diagrams, charts and visualizations in your post?It is possible and guess what? It‚Äôs not that difficult thanks to Mermaid.All you need to keep in mind is you‚Äôll have to wrap your Mermaid markup in a div with class mermaid.Here is a simple example of a basic flowchart, &lt;div class=\"mermaid\"&gt;graph LR    A[Hard edge] --&gt;|Link text| B(Round edge)    B --&gt; C{Decision}    C --&gt;|One| D[Result one]    C --&gt;|Two| E[Result two]&lt;/div&gt;The above will produce this flowchart, graph LR    A[Hard edge] --&gt;|Link text| B(Round edge)    B --&gt; C{Decision}    C --&gt;|One| D[Result one]    C --&gt;|Two| E[Result two]One more example of Mermaid‚Äôs capabilities with a sequence diagram, &lt;div class=\"mermaid\"&gt;sequenceDiagram    loop Daily query        Alice-&gt;&gt;Bob: Hello Bob, how are you?        alt is sick            Bob-&gt;&gt;Alice: Not so good :(        else is well            Bob-&gt;&gt;Alice: Feeling fresh like a daisy        end        opt Extra response            Bob-&gt;&gt;Alice: Thanks for asking        end    end&lt;/div&gt;The result is following lovely &amp; informative sequence diagram, sequenceDiagram    loop Daily query        Alice-&gt;&gt;Bob: Hello Bob, how are you?        alt is sick            Bob-&gt;&gt;Alice: Not so good :(        else is well            Bob-&gt;&gt;Alice: Feeling fresh like a daisy        end        opt Extra response            Bob-&gt;&gt;Alice: Thanks for asking        end    endInformative and intuitive! A great combo, right!?! ","categories": ["mermaid","demo"],
